parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold gasket can cause coolant to leak into the engine, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially catastrophic engine failure, which can leave the driver stranded or cause accidents.
The failure of the supercharger can cause engine fire, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: smoke rising from underneath the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Shaking of the van when applying brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to accidents or strandings.
symptoms: message center alarms indicating low fuel when tank is not empty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the door can cause accidents or injuries.
The failure of the power sliding door can cause injury or trapping of passengers, especially children, as it may not stop or reverse when encountering resistance.
symptoms: The power sliding door closes unexpectedly
causing injury or trapping of passengers; the door may not respond to the sensor or override button; the door may open or close intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rusting and Corrosion of Hood and Body
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting and corrosion of the hood and body can lead to structural weakening, compromising the safety of the vehicle and its occupants in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Rusting and corrosion on the hood
and on the body of the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the welding at the base of the driver's seat can cause the seat to move or become detached, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Welding failure at the base of the driver's seat
causing the seat to move or become detached.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the vehicle's occupants may not receive the necessary protection.
symptoms: airbags fail to deploy in a crash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a problem with the airbag system, which can lead to a failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a crash.
The failure of seatbelts can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the vehicle's occupants may not be properly restrained in the event of a crash.
